An **anagram** is a word or phrase formed by rearranging the letters of a different word or phrase.
So in the given question we need to count the frequecy of letter which are different.
**APPROACH**
First counted the frequecy of charachters in s and then counted the frequecy of t and in count variable store the mod (mean the positive value) of the difference
`

int minSteps(string s, string t) {
		unordered_map<char, int> mp;
        int n=s.size();
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
            mp[s[i]]++;
        n=t.size();
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
            mp[t[i]]--;
        int cnt=0;
        for(auto i:mp)
            cnt+=abs(i.second);
        return cnt;
    }`
	**Time Complexity:** for both the string we are going to every letter once, therefore it is O(N).
	**Space Complexity:** here we are using unordered_map to store frequecy of every letter in string so at we can have all english letter in the string, therfore it is O(26) or O(1).
	Do like it if this you in any way!

