solutions.content:
- Approach
          Firstly, I create two unordered map(m,n) and declare cnt variable and store those characters in s into m map and store those characters in t into n map.
          Now, I firstly traverse m map and I check those elements which is present in both map and add difference of those both maps of that character into cnt variable and if that character is not  present in n map then I add simply frequency in cnt variable.
          After traversing of m map I traverse n map and now I add frequency of n map of that character which is not present in m map I mean those character which is present only in n map.
          Now, I simply return cnt varible.

# Complexity
- **Time complexity: O(distinct elements in s * distinct elements in t)**
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- **Space complexity: O(distinct elements in s) + O( * distinct elements in t)**
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int minSteps(string s, string t) {
        unordered_map<char,int> m,n;
        int cnt=0;
        for(int i=0;i<s.size();i++)
        {
            m[s[i]]++;
        }
        for(int j=0;j<t.size();j++)
        {
            n[t[j]]++;
        }
        for(auto i : m)
        {
            if(n[i.first]>0)
            {
                cnt+=(max(m[i.first],n[i.first])-min(m[i.first],n[i.first]));
            }
            else{
                cnt+=m[i.first];
            }
        }
        for(auto i : n)
        {
            if(m[i.first]==0)
            {
                cnt+=n[i.first];
            }
        }
        return cnt;
    }
};
```
