# Intuition
Bring out the common characters count from the two strings

# Approach
To solve this problem, the basic idea is to calculate the count of characters that are common to both the strings, For this you can use a data structure such as map.
Note: We are only concerned with the numbers of the common characters and not the characters itself.
First iterate through the first string and store it in data structure
Next, iterate through the second string and check if it was present in data structure, if present increment the count
After the loops end the result can be calculated by difference of the string length and common characters.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
$O(N)$

- Space complexity:
$O(N)$

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int minSteps(string s, string t) {
        unordered_map<char,int> mp;
        int common=0;
        for(auto& it:s)
        mp[it]++;
        for(auto& it:t)
        {
            if(mp[it])
            {
                mp[it]--;
                common++;
            }
        }
        return s.size()+t.size()-2*common;
    }
};
```

