Again. Focus on fundamentals. It should be obvious that operations, where the characters are added and everything doens't matter. For two strings to be anagrams of each other, they need to contain the same characters. Okay great. But how do we contain the same characters? Just count what characters occur in each string, and get the diff and then sum all the diff up. 

One handy trick is to subtract the elements and keep the absolute difference. 


# Approach

1. Count characters in both the strings.
2. Sum the absolute difference. That is the result.


