This will result in TLE.
See the problem statement. It clearly says that:
![image.png](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/05fc1f3f-ed20-43ee-bbb3-e9826e357a49_1678172112.3413932.png)

So, we cannot directly go with the iterative approach.

<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach

This is an application of binary search. We should try to include binary search. 
**But how?**
**What will be the low and high variables?**

The value of time is very high. So, we better think of this as the high and low value. Then for current time value, we can iterate the loop to calculate the trips completed by each bus.

If the current time is **t** and a bus requires **bt** time to complete a trip, then by t time the bus will complete $$\frac{t}{bt}$$ trips.
For example let's say t = 5. and bus trip completion time is $$bt = 2$$.
Then, by time $$t = 5$$, the bus will be able to complete $$5/2 = 2$$ trips.

# Binary Search:

``` Java []
class Solution {
    public long minimumTime(int[] time, int totalTrips) {
        long lowestTime = 1;
        long maxTime = 100000000000000L;
        while(lowestTime < maxTime){
            long mid = lowestTime + (maxTime-lowestTime)/2;
            if(tripsCompleted(time, mid) >= totalTrips){
                maxTime = mid;
            }
            else{
                lowestTime = mid+1;
            }
        }
        return lowestTime;
    }

    private long tripsCompleted(int[] time, long currentTime){
        long totalTrips = 0;
        for(int t : time){
            long tmp = (long) t;
            totalTrips += (currentTime/tmp);
        }
        return totalTrips;
    }
}

```

This problem has a flaw. This will be less efficient. A more efficient solution is:

# Efficient Binary Search - [Beats 94%]

``` Java []
class Solution {
    public long minimumTime(int[] time, int totalTrips) {
        long lowestTime = 1;
        long maxTime = 100000000000000L;
        while(lowestTime < maxTime){
            long mid = lowestTime + (maxTime-lowestTime)/2;
            long tripsDone = tripsCompleted(time, mid, totalTrips);
            if(tripsDone >= totalTrips){
                maxTime = mid;
            }
            else{
                lowestTime = mid+1;
            }
        }
        return lowestTime;
    }

    private long tripsCompleted(int[] time, long currentTime, int totalTrips){
        long tripsDone = 0;
        for(int t : time){
            long tmp = (long) t;
            tripsDone += (currentTime/tmp);
            // instead of iterating the loop any further, break the loop.
            if(tripsDone >= totalTrips ){
                break;
            }
        }
        return tripsDone;
    }
}
```

