# Intuition
So we need to find the min time to complete the totaltrips.We already know the time for each bus to complete one trip.From it we can find the range of time to complete the totalTrips;
# Approach
First we will find the range of possible time,
mintime=min value in time * totalTrips;
(form constraints it is clear that both time[i]and totalTrips has a min value of 1.Therefore mintime=1 always);
maxtime=max value in time * totalTrips;
(this we will find by extracting max value in vector time)

Now we have our time range(start=mintime and end=maxtime) now we will apply binary search  and check if this mid (time) can complete totalTrips.
if YES than store it in ans and do maxtime=mid-1;
else mintime=mid+1;

To check if time is feasible we will create a function "isSafe" which find the value of total trip which can be completed in time(value of mid); 

