# Intuition
We need to minimize the time so we can think of applying binary search on answer concept and create a minimum and maximum limit on time possible and try to minimize the time by applying binary search on that interval.

# Approach
We create a lower limit (l) on time which will be the lowest time in the array and an upper limit (h) on time which will be ( lowest time in the array * totaltrips ), because the least maximum time in which totaltrips can be completed will be the lowest time in the array mutiplied by totaltrips. Now we have an interval on time. We calculate the middle value and check whether it can be our possible answer or not. If it is a valid answer then we store it and we move h = mid-1 and we check for a better answer in the left interval. If it cannot be a valid answer then we check for an answer in the right interval(a larger time can become an answer). In the end we return our answer.  

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(NlogN) where N is length of times array


# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    long long minimumTime(vector<int>& time, int totalTrips) {
        sort(time.begin(), time.end());
        long long l = time[0];
        long long h = (long long)((long long)time[0]*(long long)totalTrips);
        long long mid = l+(h-l)/2;
        long long ans = LONG_LONG_MAX;
        while(l <= h)
        {
            mid = l+(h-l)/2;
            if(check(mid, time, totalTrips))
            {
                ans = mid;
                h = mid-1;
            }else
            {
                l = mid+1;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }

    bool check(long long time, vector<int>& times, int totaltrips)
    {
        bool valid = false;
        int currenttrips = 0;
        for(int i = 0;i < times.size(); i++)
        {
            if(times[i] > time)
            {
                break;
            }
            currenttrips += (time/times[i]);
            if(currenttrips >= totaltrips)
            {
                valid = true;
                break;
            }
        }
        return valid;
    }
};
```

