# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We can find whether the totalTrips can be completed in given time in O(n) complexity. We just need the appropriate time. If we have minTime and maxTime then we can easily find the appropriate time in O(logn) complexity.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. First sort the time array. time[0] will be the smallest element and time[n-1] will be the greatest element.
2. The maxTime to complete all trips will be -> time[n-1] * totalTrips.
3. The minTime will be 1 day.
4. int mid = (minTime + maxTime) / 2; If totalTrips are completed within mid time then maxTime = mid. Else we require more time. Then minTime = mid + 1.
5. This process will be repeated until minTime < maxTime. Once the condition fails we will return minTime. The complexity of this process will be O(logn).
6. To check if the totalTrips are completed within mid time, we will iterate through loop and check if summation of mid/ time[i] is greater than mid time. If it is grater the totalTrips can't be completed in mid time and we will return false. If the summation sis less than mid time then we will return true. The complexity of this process will be O(n).
7. The total complexity of the solution will be O(nlogn).

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(nlogn)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:O(n)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

