solutions.content:
## When we will change tyre?

We will change tyre when current Time for a Lap is >= f + change time.

Because by changing tyre we are using the same or less time than the time required for a consecutive lap without change, and also it will benefit the future laps too.

Ex: f = 2, r = 3, changeTime = 10
Lap1 : Cost = 2, Total = 2
Lap2 : Cost = Cost of Last Lap * r = 6, Total = 8
Lap3 : Cost 6*3 = 18 , Now 18>change TIme+f
Hence we will change tyre

## Approach:

dp[i] denotes the min time to travel i laps.

We first fill the dp without changing tyres and then modify and fill the remaining states of dp by recurrence relation:

<b>dp[i] = min(dp[i] ,changeTime + dp[j] + dp[i-j])

Basically we are breaking i laps into parts j and (i-j) laps (i>=j).
And we have already calculated dp[j] and dp[i-j].

## Code:
```
typedef long long ll;

class Solution {
public:

    void fillDPWithoutChange(vector<ll>& dp, int changeTime, vector<vector<int>>& tires)
    {
        for (vector<int>& currTyre : tires)
        {
            ll f = currTyre[0];
            ll r = currTyre[1];
            dp[1] = min(dp[1], f);
            ll lastLapTime = f;
            ll totalTime = f;
            ll lapCount = 2;
            while (lastLapTime * r < f + changeTime && lapCount < dp.size())
			//we can prove that this loop will not run many times because we are
			//moving in powers of r and even a small r like 2 will terminate this
			//loop under 20 iterations.
            {
                ll currLapTime = lastLapTime * r;
                totalTime += currLapTime;
                dp[lapCount] = min(dp[lapCount], totalTime);
                lastLapTime = currLapTime;
                lapCount++;
            }
        }
    }

    void modifyDPforChange(vector<ll>& dp, int changeTime, vector<vector<int>>& tires)
    {
        for (ll i = 1; i < dp.size(); ++i)
        {
            for (ll j = 1; j <= i; ++j)
            {
                dp[i] = min(dp[i], changeTime + dp[j] + dp[i - j]);
            }
        }
    }

    int minimumFinishTime(vector<vector<int>>& tires, int changeTime, int numLaps) {
        vector<ll> dp(numLaps + 1, LLONG_MAX);
        dp[0] = 0;
        fillDPWithoutChange(dp, changeTime, tires);
        modifyDPforChange(dp, changeTime, tires);
        return dp[numLaps];
    }
};
```

Time Complexity : O(max(numLaps^2,number of tyres))
Space: O(numLaps)

