solutions.content:
we have to precompute some info and then it is DP

First of all, it is never optimal for a tire to be used for more than 20 laps, so we precompute the best time for the `i` consecutive laps.
Once we have that info, we can solve it either with a `dp[n]` or `dp[20]`. Here I am presenting both.

I came up with the `dp[20]` way first because it is a bit more intuitive, but `dp[n]` is a bit easier to code. Both have the same time complexity and get AC in 20ms. 

#### Solution 1: Space O(n)
For each index `i`, consider from index `i-1 ... i-20` as the starting point, and we change tires at `i`. 
Then we have `dp[i] = min(dp[i], cost[j]+dp[i-j-1]+changeTime)`
We will always include `changeTime` one extra time at the end, so subtract it.
```Java
class Solution {
    public int minimumFinishTime(int[][] tires, int changeTime, int numLaps) {
        int[] cost = new int[20];
        int INF = (int)1e9;
        Arrays.fill(cost, INF);
        for (int[] t : tires){
            for (int i = 0,sum=t[0],cur=t[0]; i < 20; i++,cur*=t[1],sum+=cur){
                cost[i] = Math.min(cost[i], sum);
                if (sum+1L*cur*t[1]>= 1e6){
                    break;
                }
            }
        }
        int[] dp = new int[numLaps];
        Arrays.fill(dp, INF);
        for (int i = 0; i < numLaps; i++){
            for (int j = 0; j <= Math.min(i,19); j++){
                dp[i]=Math.min(dp[i], (j==i?0:dp[i-j-1])+cost[j]+changeTime);
            }
        }
        return dp[numLaps-1]-changeTime;
    }
}
```
#### Solution 2: Space O(1)
Let `dp[i]` be the number of consecutive `i` laps thus far. 
Then we have: `next[i] = dp[i-1] - cost[i-1] + cost[i]` and `next[0] = min(next[0], dp[j]+changeTime+cost[0])`.
No need to compensate for the extra changeTime like solution 1, but we will have to loop through all the consesctive laps (max at 20) and return the min of it.
```Java
class Solution {
    public int minimumFinishTime(int[][] tires, int changeTime, int numLaps) {
        int[] cost = new int[20];
        int INF = (int)1e9;
        Arrays.fill(cost, INF);
        for (int[] t : tires){
            for (int i = 0,sum=t[0],cur=t[0]; i < 20; i++,cur*=t[1],sum+=cur){
                cost[i] = Math.min(cost[i], sum);
                if (sum+1L*cur*t[1]>= 1e6){
                    break;
                }
            }
        }

        int[] dp = new int[20];
        Arrays.fill(dp, INF);
        dp[0]=cost[0];
        for (int i = 1 ; i < numLaps; i++){
            int tmp = dp[0];
            dp[0]=INF;
            for (int j = 19; j >= 0; j--){
                dp[0]=Math.min((j==0?tmp:dp[j])+changeTime+cost[0], dp[0]);
                // next[0]=Math.min(dp[j]+changeTime+cost[0], next[0]);
                if (j>0){
                    dp[j]=(j==1?tmp:dp[j-1])-cost[j-1]+cost[j];
                    // next[j]=dp[j-1]-cost[j-1]+cost[j];
                }
            }
            // dp=next;
        }
        return Arrays.stream(dp).min().getAsInt();
    }
}
```

