Spent more than 3 days understanding the solutions and watching videos on youtube.

Takeway: How to break down a complex problem provided some hints are given.


# Intuition
Central idea is when to change the tire.
What data is needed:
Max number of laps a tire can be used before the change time + tire[0] is better than the lap time using the same tire.
Also while running the DP what is the max we need to look back in best[] -- optimization

# Approach
preprocess the best times to run 18 laps for all tires.
Run DP and calculate min time for ith lap.
Code is commented for thought process and revision in future.

# Complexity
O(num laps * O(18)) -- for DP
O (size of tires * O(18)) for preprocess.

- Space complexity:
O(18), O(num laps)

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int minimumFinishTime(int[][] tires, int changeTime, int numLaps) {


        int[] best = new int[18];
        Arrays.fill(best, Integer.MAX_VALUE);
        int maxLapsTireCanBeUsed = 0;

        // preprocess
        // using each tire fill/update the best times for 18 laps.
        for (int[] tire : tires){
            int totalTime = tire[0], lapTime = tire[0];
            //using a tire update best as far as the time to use the tire is a good option
            // than changing the tire by taking change time penality
            // we do this only for 18 laps as after 18 laps the changetime penality even for 
            // a max value of 10^5 + F MAX of 10^5 will be smaller than the lap time if
            // the same tire is used
            for (int j = 1; j < 18; j++){
                best[j] = Math.min(best[j], totalTime);
                //update laptime and total time for this lap.
                lapTime *= tire[1];
                totalTime += lapTime;

                maxLapsTireCanBeUsed = Math.max(maxLapsTireCanBeUsed, j);
                // if laptime is more than the time to change time + tire[0] .. break.
                if (lapTime > changeTime + tire[0])
                    break;

            }
        }

        int[] dp = new int[numLaps+1];
        Arrays.fill(dp, Integer.MAX_VALUE);
        dp[0] = 0;

        for (int i = 1; i <= numLaps; i++){
            for (int j = i - 1; j >= 0 && i - j <= maxLapsTireCanBeUsed; j--){
                // if (i - j > maxLapsTireCanBeUsed){
                //     break;
                // }
                dp[i] = Math.min(dp[i], dp[j] + changeTime + best[i - j]);
            }
        }
        return dp[numLaps] - changeTime;
    }
}
/*
number of laps  <= 1000
fi  and changetime max can be between 1 .. 10^5
ri can be between 2 .. 10^5
fi+ri*2^(lap# - 1)
options min (changetime + tire[i][0], tire[i][0] + tire[i][1]*2^lap# - 1)

for each tire
    for each lap update the best we can get without changing the tire
    ex 2-3 , ct - 5
    lap 1 - 2 * 3^0, -- 2
    lap 2 - min (2 * 3^1, 2+5) -- (6,7) -- 6
    lap 3 - 2 * 3^2, 2+5 -- (11, 7) -- 7

    ex 3-4 , ct - 5
    lap1 - 3 *4^0 = 3 -- 3
