# Intuition
Inspired by https://leetcode.com/problems/minimum-time-to-finish-the-race/solutions/1802498/pretreatment-dp/

The intutiton is that every lap your car takes with the same tires, the slower it gets. That means new tires result in best performance, however changing tires takes time. We have to stick with the same tires until it makes sense to switch. We have, however, different sets of tires, which makes our decision process more complex.

# Approach

We have to find the best combination of tire re-use and tire replacement that will give us the best finish time. Using DFS with memoization (top-down dynamic programming) we can look at the topmost level what is the best performing streak of reused tires followed by subsequent tire exchanges:
```
for(int lp = 1; lp <= Math.Min(maxLap, numLap); lp++)
    finLap[numLap] = Math.Min(finLap[numLap], best[lp] + changeTime + DfsFindMinTime(numLap - lp, changeTime));
```
"best" array is pre-computed and will contain the best performing single use tire streak for a certain amount of laps. Note that its computation has an optimization
```
 currTime < fI + changeTime
```

that prevents our compuations to go all the way to numLaps if we get to a point where changing tires and starting over makes more sense than keep going with the same tires. That also explains the upper bound of the for loop of the DP method:
```
Math.Min(maxLap, numLap)
```

Basically, if there's no tire set that can go all the way to numLaps, we just need to try up to maxLap (the longest we can stick with a tire set and still get optimal performance).

# Code
```
public class Solution {
    private int[] finLap, best;
    private int maxLap = 1;
    public int MinimumFinishTime(int[][] tires, int changeTime, int numLaps) {    
        finLap = new int[numLaps+1];
        best = new int[numLaps+1];
        Array.Fill(best, Int32.MaxValue);
        Array.Fill(finLap, Int32.MaxValue);
        FindBest(tires, changeTime, numLaps);  
        return DfsFindMinTime(numLaps, changeTime);
    }
    private void FindBest(int[][] tires, int changeTime, int numLaps){ 
            foreach(var t in tires){
                int fI = t[0], rI = t[1];
                int time = fI, currTime = fI;
                for(int lp = 1; lp<=numLaps && currTime < fI + changeTime; lp++){
                    best[lp] = Math.Min(time, best[lp]);
                    maxLap = Math.Max(maxLap, lp);
                    currTime *= rI;
                    time += currTime;
                }
            }
    }
    private int DfsFindMinTime(int numLap, int changeTime){
        if(numLap == 0){
            return -changeTime;
        }
        if(finLap[numLap] != Int32.MaxValue) return finLap[numLap];
        for(int lp = 1; lp <= Math.Min(maxLap, numLap); lp++)
          finLap[numLap] = Math.Min(finLap[numLap], best[lp] + changeTime +          DfsFindMinTime(numLap - lp, changeTime));
        return finLap[numLap];
    } 
}
```

