# Approach
Use a hashtable to store target and count values

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n) traverse array one time and also hashtable to find max count

- Space complexity:
O(n) need extra memory using HashTable

# Code
```
public class Solution {
    public int MostFrequent(int[] nums, int key) {

        Dictionary<int, int> map = new Dictionary<int, int>();
        int i = 0;

        while(i < nums.Length)
        {
            if(nums[i] == key && i + 1 < nums.Length)
            {
                if(map.ContainsKey(nums[i + 1]))
                {
                    map[nums[i + 1]]++;
                }
                else
                {
                    map.Add(nums[i + 1], 1);
                }
            }

            i++;
        }

        int max = 0;
        int result = 0;

        foreach(var item in map)
        {
            if(item.Value > max)
            {
                max = item.Value;
                result = item.Key;
            }
        }

        return result;

    }
}
```

